race.comment: SKY OF GOLD (13) is nearing a win with three solid runs to date, including a close-up fourth latest. Has a nice weight with the claim and off the low draw will give a sight. ARGYLL DIAMOND (8) turned in an eye-catching run last time when hit the line well for second. Fitter again and over the extra trip again looks hard to hold out. NORTHERN CHILD (6) was in the market on debut and found the line strongly to finish third, beaten less than two lengths. Has good upside and can feature again with any luck from the wide draw. PARTY DAY (10) tried to lead throughout last time and gave a sight but cold manage only second. Has placed 2/4 so far and off the tricky gate will surge forward and give a sight again. UP TO TORI (14) made debut on heavy ground and was safely held and put away again. Brought back for firmer going and well worth another try.
